caption: Delicious and inspiring food..

Desperate times. Desperate behavior. But at the customer's expense?! Don't think so!  On New Year's Eve, we ordered take out from Osteria del Pastaio. A man named Christiane took our phone order at 4pm for 7pm pick up. The receipt says he charged our credit card at 4:04 pm for the full order. We wanted to pick up the order without coming into contact with staff due to Covid.  When taking our phone order, Christiane asked me if I would leave a tip. We try and support local restaurants, but I politely said no tip please. Christiane became angry, arguing to leave a tip for take out/pick up. Ten minutes before my husband picked up the order, I called ahead to confirm the order. An Irene answered and said there was no order placed. This despite the receipt confirming our cc was charged at 4:04 pm. She said she would ready the order.  My husband arrived at 7pm and they said there was no order placed, made my husband wait outside in the cold for 15 minutes while they "prepared our order", then made my husband come inside, call me using their phone to see what happened. Christiane then took the phone from my husband and said to me, "You're the person that left no tip for take out, so we don't have your order." Christiane asked me who I spoke with to place the order. I reminded him it was he who took our order. Christiane then became extremely unprofessional, belligerent, angry, carrying on about no tip before hanging up on me. It is 7:30 pm on NYE. He finally said he would ready our order.  We asked to speak to the manager/owner. Neither Christiane or Irene would put us in touch, but said she was there. Upon returning home, the order was messed up/wrong. We got sick from the food. We feel their intent was to make us squirm/give us a really hard time since they knew it was the eleventh hour on NYE.  Since they shielded the owner, we truly hope she reads this and does the right thing. All this to simply try to support our local business. Christiane and Irene: Please! No customer deserves to be treated/harassed in this manner! There's too much competition from which to choose! Not good for your brand! We also work hard for our living and it is the customer's decision whether to tip or not for take out!

I made reservations earlier in the week on OpenTable for outdoor seating for 3 at 7:30 PM. On the day of, our uber cancelled at the last minute and we had to wait for a new ride. I contacted the restaurant at 7:30 and told them the situation and that we would be about 10 minutes late. The hostess said that she would make a note that we were running late and she’d see us soon. Upon arriving at the restaurant the host immediately told us that they have a 10 minute grace period and they’d given away our table. I pulled out my phone to check the time at it showed 7:39 PM. I told him we were within the 10 minute grace period but the host said that they had given our table away but we were free to dine inside. I told him that I didn’t want to eat inside due to COVID and he assured me that the restaurant was completely empty except for staff. I again told him I didn’t want to eat inside and that it also wasn’t really the ambiance we were going for. Extremely disappointed.

I stumbled upon this great restaurant by accident one day.  My meal was great, and I decided to return for dinner the next night.  My experience has been deliciously consistent for every meal I've had thus far.   I'm staying at the Sofitel Hotel intermittently for six months and, this place has become my go-to dinner spot.  Aside from the food, the staff is delightful to be around.  In the short few weeks of visiting, I've seen many regulars there.  All the patrons seem to have a fun and friendly relationship with all of the staff.  There is a great positive vibe there, I appreciate that.  Osteria Del Pastaio is a place worth experiencing. You will not go wrong.

I asked for garlic and added some Parmesan which helped but did not fix it. The Caesar salad was very fresh but the dressing was almost non-existent and I had to ask for more which improved the taste. Given its $12 price tag oh, I would have expected more.

Loved our visit here.  My girlfriend and I had a lovely early dinner and thoroughly enjoyed our stay. Our server Julia was lovely and the food was very good.  Loved the olive spread with bread to start.  Followed by tomato soup and shrimp with avocado salad. Our Entrees were the branzino which was delicious as the linguine with clams was quite good. Dined here last night with my wife and we couldn't have been more pleased.  Our server Julia was just fantastic and so helpful and professional.  Her suggestions were spot on.  We started with the Calamari and Wild Mushroom appetizers and cleaned the plates.  For a main dish we had the Veal Scaloppini with lemon caper sauce and an Eggplant Parmesan dish.  Both were perfect.  The manager stopped over to check on us a few times which was a very nice touch.  I would also suggest the Lemon Drop Martini to get your meal going.  We will certainly be back for both the food and the top notch service.

The food was quite good with the portions on small side. I didn’t get pictures of the entire meal. The one I am posting is of the hearts of palm salad. I found it to be delightful. It was a simple salad of chopped hearts of palm, avocado and asparagus in a vinaigrette with a hint of truffle oil. It was followed by spaghetti with seafood which was good. Some of the seafood was a touch over-cooked. Lastly, we had dessert which was our least favorite course. The service was great. I’d probably go back.

During when we were in chicago we went to an amazing italian restaurant named osteria del pastalo and it was awesome. We were greeted nicely. We were then led to our table which after this our waiter took extra time to introduce himself and was super nice and respectful. His name was george. He was very nice and professional and had all of the qualities you could ask for in a waiter. He was also very respectful about my dads diet and helped him out. My family was impressed by his nice attitude and personality. The ambiance was exceptional. You feel very comfortable eating at this restaurant. The charis were very comfy and nice. It was also very easy to move around. Everybody else was really enjoying themselves as they ate. They seemed to be enjoying their meals. For my dinner i had the gnocchi with pesto sauce which was exceptional. Everything from the flavors to the plating to the visual appeal was amazing. I don't have words to say how amazing this place was. It was so clean that you would feel terrible if you got a dot of food on the floor. They even brought the chef out to meet us and we told him how amazing the food was. If you are ever in chicago make sure you stop by osteria del pastaio for the best in chicago italien cuisine.

This place deserves to be mentioned along the best Italian restaurants in the Chi. We started with a Caesar salad which was unique and fresh tasting, but the next course was where the fun really started. A mild truffle ravioli with a sweet pumpkin filling started us off; we also enjoyed a rigatoni noodle with a simple but perfectly spiced arrabiata sauce. For our main course we had a huge half chicken for a very reasonable price, in an amazingly savory sauce with some lightly fried potato wedges. I will definitely be back and highly recommend all the dishes I tried!

We came for happy hour, and we were seated in the bar, at first we were the only ones. It was probably 20 min before anyone bothered to come over to us. Literally two bartenders walked past us multiple times before one stopped and seemed to have zero patience with us while we ordered. The plates were incredibly small for how expensive it was and my cocktail was not good. In the meantime other customers came in and had the "regular" menu and were waited on immediately. At the end we were given the wrong bill by the bartender and he promptly walked off. He never bothered to come back so I had to walk over and ask a manager for help. We won't return, it definitely felt like we were ignored solely because we came for happy hour. If you're unhappy serving happy hour then why have one...?
